title: Communauté d'agglomération du Centre Littoral
text:
<a href="Communaut%C3%A9%20d%27agglom%C3%A9ration">Communauté d'agglomération</a> du Centre Littoral is an <a href="Communes%20of%20France%23Intercommunality">intercommunal</a> structure, centred on the <a href="Communes%20of%20France">city</a> of <a href="Cayenne">Cayenne</a>. It is located in the <a href="French%20Guiana">French Guiana</a> <a href="Overseas%20departments%20and%20regions%20of%20France">overseas department and region</a> of <a href="France">France</a>. It was created in January 2012. Its seat is in Cayenne. Its population was 138,920 in 2017, of which 61,268 in Cayenne proper.
